headline: New power management chips from TI maximize protection, density and efficiency for modern data centers
summary: Texas Instruments (TI) (Nasdaq: TXN) today debuted new power-management chips to support the rapidly growing power needs of modern data centers. As the adoption of high-performance computing and artificial intelligence (AI) increases, data centers require more power-dense and efficient solutions. TI's new TPS1685 is the industry's first 48V integrated hot-swap eFuse with power-path protection to support data center hardware and processing needs.
